Xespok, SamSite, luwenzhe, HEX77, Red_Zombie, tianxia, shuwang, Before, whte, sosei, lingdodo.
about the gameserver, I guess we will have to wait some time
Now, lets begin with lesson part
d3 opening, this variant can come from two 5th moves
however, this situation after 8 moves has always confused me.
it was so popular in old times,
long before you all began to play renju,
but yet, there are no answers
is it better for black or white
does anyone have answer to that?
so let me ask in other words
have you played this variant before?
looks quite natural sequence of moves
maybe h10 is weakest of them
and at that time I chose this 9th move,
The common struggle usually began from here like this
but some variants, such as this 12th
I chose to play another 9th move
because repeating the path of my own old game is so dangerous
because that is likely what the WC opponent hopes and plans for
yes. others maybe have studied your old games carefully
in WC level, nearly everybody is doing good homework
even I changed the 9th move, I was not very well prepared there.
the opponent, a very strong, young, talented player
he played a lot on our game server two months ago
he was quite nervous in his first WC, but yet he did well and got the 4th place
also, it was the first time he and I met in tournament.
He was scaring most of his opponents with his i6 opening gamble
but as from Kawamura's lesson, you all saw black has sure win.
anyway, d3 opening was between us,
I knew he played something about this 9th move several times before,
and it has been quite popular in Russia recently.
But I did not have time to check them.
Therefore, I went into this variant with the hope, that I will have the inspiration, and good thinking.
Do you know where he played?
And he played it so fast,
It is a hard moment in WCs.
You know you are playing your opponents favorite position.
without having any knowledge of it myself
Thousands of thoughts came through my mind.
I tried to think of what he might think.
I thought "if he has counted all, it also means he has considered active play of blacks, which likely fails in the end, and white is good later below"
So, by that thinking I felt worried
because if black cannot have a good plan here,
Also, I was thinking of passive style
but I realized, then white gets the initiative forever
no matter what, I must play actively,
because, after all, his preparation might not be perfect
So I made natural start with h10
After this move I began to believe in my win
who wants to show win here?
if no cut, i would play 36 down
maybe safe style is better here
would anyone want to show idea for black's attack?
did you see it all from the start, or just wild attack?
I am sorry. I will behave.
tianxia and lingdodo both good job
He was spending most of the time thinking between two options
which one you think is stronger move?
the day of double cp, lets be double active
Well, after maybe 1 hour of thinking,
Lets take a look at g8 first
Can you think of the reason,
why Chingin didnt like this variant?
who can show black's attack plan?
There are many plans in fact
I hope you can show me at least one
luwenzhe, SamSite, Before, tianxia, shuwang, Red_Zombie, lingdodo, sosei, Xespok.
so, this 19 was one of the win ways
but I didnt study this way that much
Therefore, he played 18 here, the strongest.
Now it was my turn to think over 1 hour
who can show black win, say me
that was the idea of move 19
to be sufficient enough for defense,
and yet be so powerful attack builder
you may think, this 19 is safer
now black does not have the j9 link to right wing
ithought white has vct threat black should defend
why I didnt play 19 to g-6
because I can always play there later
the more material I can keep open on upper side,
the more different choices I have later for its usage
Now I began the attack, with logical moves
"we're breaking our broacast, because Ando Merite steps!"
i no longer had use for j9 connection
so I began to collect powers to lower side
He does not let me take g5
the main support here is the g10
this is what makes the attack so strong
having not much time left by then, if I remember right.
Black is in full attack now/
live four is in I line?

and solve this issue here at gome
now, we will end the lesson.
you were few here today, but active, and i enjoyed it a lot
